extends layouts/root

block content
  article.doc
    header.doc-head
      p.doc-eyebrow Documentation
      h1#what-is-entipic What is Entipic?
    p Entipic is a service offering every subject or topic — Google, Barack Obama, Paris — a representative image that can be freely used by any application.
    p The idea is simple, and easiest to explain by analogy: #[a(href='https://www.gravatar.com', target='_blank', rel='noopener') Gravatar] gives every email address a picture. Entipic gives every topic a picture.
    p The service is particularly useful for news sites and blogs that want to associate a representative image with each tag or topic.

    h2#how-to-use Using the service
    p To attach an image to a topic, build a URL in this format:
    pre.code-block
      code http://cdn.entipic.com/[language]-[country]/[size]/[topic].jpg

    dl.params
      div.param
        dt
          code [language]
        dd Two-letter language code (e.g. en, fr, ro).
      div.param
        dt
          code [country]
        dd Two-letter country code (e.g. us, fr, ro). Optional but recommended.
      div.param
        dt
          code [size]
        dd
          | Requested image size — one of:
          br
          span.size-chip #[code a] 50×50
          span.size-chip #[code b] 100×100
          span.size-chip #[code c] 150×150
          span.size-chip #[code d] 200×200
          span.size-chip #[code e] 250×250
          span.size-chip #[code f] 300×300
          span.size-chip #[code x] 25×25
      div.param
        dt
          code [topic]
        dd The topic name, 2–50 characters. Casing and separators don't matter — #[code barack-obama], #[code Barack Obama] and #[code Barack_Obama] all resolve to the same topic.

    h2#examples Examples
    ul.examples-list
      li
        code http://cdn.entipic.com/en/barack-obama.jpg
        span 50×50 picture for Barack Obama (English).
      li
        code http://cdn.entipic.com/en/c/twitter.jpg
        span 150×150 picture for Twitter.
      li
        code http://cdn.entipic.com/fr/b/paris.jpg
        span 100×100 picture for Paris (French).
      li
        code http://cdn.entipic.com/ro-ro/b/Adrian_Ursu.jpg
        span 100×100 picture for Adrian Ursu (Romania, Romanian).

    .note
      strong Note.
      |  Only #[code [topic]] is required, but providing a language code is strongly recommended, especially for short or ambiguous names.

    h2#how-it-works How it works
    p For every request the system returns an image associated with the topic. If the topic is unknown, a temporary 1×1 pixel image is returned while the system searches for the best match in the background. Subsequent requests will receive the discovered picture.
    p Entipic respects image copyright — sources are tracked and attributed, and most images come from Wikipedia.
